## 1. Dataset Details (VERY IMPORTANT)

### 📊 Core dataset info
- Total drugs (nodes): 19,830
- Total interactions (rows/known edges source): 1,455,276
- Source: DrugBank XML and derived CSVs
- DrugBank metadata in XML header: version="5.1", exported-on="2026-01-04"
- Additional merged datasets:
  - No clearly integrated external benchmark dataset found in serving path
  - Optional enrichment script exists (PubChem-based in data_enrichment.py), but not guaranteed complete in current serving snapshot

### 🧪 Feature availability (ACTUAL use)
- SMILES: ✅ used where available
  - Used in graph_builder.py (chemical feature extraction for node features if present)
  - Used post-hoc in services/feature_importance.py for chemical similarity
- ATC codes: ✅/⚠️ partially used
  - Used post-hoc for ATC similarity in services/feature_importance.py
  - Not clearly used as a core training feature in graph_builder.py
- Target/enzyme data: ⚠️ partial
  - Target-like overlap proxy from mechanism text is used post-hoc
  - Explicit enzyme-overlap module is not implemented as a dedicated model feature
- Text descriptions: ✅ used
  - TF-IDF from description + mechanism in graph_builder.py
- Side effects: ❌ not implemented as a dedicated feature in training/inference path

---

## 2. Task Definition (Exact Outputs)

- Binary interaction prediction: ✅ yes
- Severity classification (3-class): ✅ yes (Minor/Moderate/Major)
- Confidence score: ✅ yes (regression head)

How confidence is trained:
- Confidence head uses MSE loss against edge_labels (same binary labels used for interaction positives/negatives).
- Therefore confidence target is not an independently curated clinical confidence label.
- It behaves as a proxy confidence objective rather than a separate labeled confidence dataset.

Novelty implication:
- Confidence head is present (good), but supervision design is weak for publication unless justified or redesigned.

---

## 3. Model Architecture (Code-Level Detail)

### 🔧 Encoder
- PyTorch Geometric GATConv is used (gcn_model.py)
- Architecture:
  - conv1 = GATConv(input_dim, hidden_dim, heads=heads)
  - conv2 = GATConv(hidden_dim * heads, hidden_dim, heads=heads)
  - conv3 = GATConv(hidden_dim * heads, embedding_dim, heads=1, concat=False)
- Attention type:
  - Standard GATConv multi-head attention
  - Multi-head concat in first two layers
  - Final layer uses single head without concat
  - No explicit edge-aware attention variant found

### 🔧 Decoder
- Pair representation: concatenation of two node embeddings
- Combination strategy: concat (not dot-product, not bilinear)

### 🔧 Heads and losses
1. Interaction head
- MLP: Linear(2E->256) -> LeakyReLU -> Dropout -> Linear(256->128) -> LeakyReLU -> Linear(128->1)
- Loss: BCEWithLogitsLoss

2. Severity head
- MLP: Linear(2E->128) -> LeakyReLU -> Dropout -> Linear(128->64) -> LeakyReLU -> Linear(64->3)
- Loss: CrossEntropyLoss (on positive edges)

3. Confidence head
- MLP: Linear(2E->64) -> ReLU -> Linear(64->1) -> Sigmoid
- Loss: MSELoss vs edge_labels

Combined loss weighting:
- Total = interaction_loss + 0.5 * severity_loss + 0.2 * confidence_loss

---

## 4. Training Setup

Negative sampling strategy:
- Random negative sampling via torch_geometric.utils.negative_sampling
- Hard negatives: ❌ not implemented

Loss combination:
- Fixed manual weights (1.0, 0.5, 0.2)
- Learned uncertainty weighting: ❌ not implemented

Train/val/test split:
- Edge split on unique undirected edges
- Default split: train 80%, val 10%, test 10%
- Reverse edges re-added for message passing graph

